The [[Lie algebra|Lie algebra]] $$(\so(3),[\cdot,\cdot])$$ is isomorphic to $$(\R^3, \times)$$: Associate
$$
\begin{pmatrix}
  0  & -\xi_3 & \xi_2 \\
  \xi_3 & 0 & -\xi_1 \\
  -\xi_2 & \xi_1 & 0 \\
\end{pmatrix} \leftrightarrow
\begin{pmatrix} \xi_1 \\ \xi_2 \\ \xi_3 \end{pmatrix}.
$$
The standard scalar product on $$\R^3$$ transfers to $$\so(3).$$ With the above identification:
$$
\lang \xi,\eta \rang = -\tfrac{1}{2} \tr(\xi\eta).
$$
For $$x \in \R^3,$$ We also have
$$
\xi x = \xi \times x.
$$